    "body": "## Problem\r\n\r\nFixes #39017.\r\n\r\n`vim.secure.trust({ bufnr = ... })` hashes an unchanged empty buffer as a newline, so trusting an empty file by buffer does not match the empty bytes hashed by `vim.secure.read(path)`.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nHandle the unchanged empty-buffer case explicitly and hash it as `''` so buffer-based trust matches the on-disk empty file in that workflow.\r\n\r\n***NOTE***: NeoVim's modified-empty vs unmodified-empty is (and has been for a while) WIP (see #34272), so this is intentionally scoped to only unchanged, empty files which are handled unambiguously. For example, modifying an empty, untrusted file (which is allowed) will STILL run into the linked issue..\r\n",
